@startuml
' IOD(5)_Pj2_T-1 — User Story 5: Suggest Available Rooms and Time Slots

skinparam DefaultFontName Arial
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #444444
skinparam ArrowColor #444444
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFFCC
skinparam NoteBorderColor #AAAAAA

title IOD(5)_Pj2_T-1\nUS5: Suggest Available Rooms and Time Slots

start

:Prerequisite: schedule data has been imported\n(see US1 — Upload Excel File);

:Actor navigates to the Vacancy Search Page;

:Actor specifies search criteria:\n- Semester\n- Desired class duration (minutes)\n- Optional: specific room filter;

:Actor submits search;

#ADD8E6:**ref** UC_ROOM — View Room Schedule (per candidate room)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
System loads current timetable for each room\nin the selected semester;

#ADD8E6:**ref** UC_VACANCY — Vacancy Search
────────────────────────────────────────────────
System identifies open time slots that are at\nleast as long as the requested duration;

if (Vacant slots found?) then (yes)
  :System displays vacancy table listing\nroom, day, start time, end time, and duration;
  :Actor reviews available rooms and time slots;
else (no)
  :System displays "No vacant spots found" message;
endif

stop
@enduml
